product_name: NYX Professional MakeupJumbo Eye Pencil All-In-One Eyeshadow Eyeliner Pencil
summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeGive BackNYX Professional Makeup Jumbo Eye Pencil combines an eyeshadow and eyeliner all-in-one! This longwear liner features a creamy formula in many blendable shades.
details: DetailsBenefitsSharpenable multi-use eye crayon can be used as an eyeliner, eyeshadow, eyeshadow primer or highlightFeatures a creamy formula that glides on smoothly like silk and is easy to blendFormula lasts all day & does not crease or dry outAvailable in an astounding array of shades that work both day and night for any eye lookApply it to your water lines, inner corners and entire eye lidMade with a blend of mineral oil & powder, the creamy Jumbo Eye Pencils glide on effortlessly - no pulling, tugging or fadingCruelty freeItem 2139571How To UseApply NYX Professional Makeup Jumbo Eye Pencil as an eyeliner, all over mono eyeshadow, or underneath shadow as a primer. reviews.headline: OK at best
reviews.comments:
It goes on smooth & blends well & doesn't irritate my eyes, but it doesn't last.
Ulta and or NYX need to update the web entry for this though.
Yoghurt is also a completely different shade and finish in the detail photo than the product is IRL.
I'm betting the others are wrong as well.

reviews.headline: Not satisfactory
reviews.comments: I think you changed the formula on this product.   My eyes watered and itched u til I removed it.   I bought two in different colors and I am afraid to use them.

reviews.headline: would purchase again
reviews.comments: My oldest daughter loves it uses it as an eyeshadow and highlighter, so fun!

reviews.headline: Very great-need to reapply every once in a while
reviews.comments: This eyeliner is very bright and takes my makeup to the next level! However, since it is on your waterline and it isn't very permanent, you need to reapply after every other hour. What I've also noticed is that it leaves a line at the part of your skin right underneath your waterline after all the product washes out.

reviews.headline: I love these!!
reviews.comments: This is my 4th purchase of these eyeliner/eye shadow pencil.   Love the ease of using and they last long.

reviews.headline: nice colors, but disappears when blending
reviews.comments: some of the colors are great for highlighting the inner corner of your eyes or underneath your brow, but it pretty much disappears when you blend it out. the color does not stay vibrant. I personally don't mind it as much when I'm just trying to lighten up under my brow or maybe add a little bit of brightness to my cheek instead of doing a heavy glitter highlight but I would not use it as an eyeshadow pencil at all. strictly as an eyeshadow, this IMO is a major flop. I've had a couple colors and been using for a little over a year off and on and I'm just not feeling it. not to mention I didn't realize it will have to be sharpened... somehow?? will not buy again and I don't recommend buying..

reviews.headline: Nice jumbo pencil
reviews.comments: This is a nice jumbo pencil that goes on smoothly and stays on.  I usually smudge it and then highlight it with a pencil and mascara.  I wish it was a little more on the navy blue side but I make the color work.  I'm not sure how this will hold up after being sharpened - we'll see!!

reviews.headline: Love it!

reviews.headline: Limited color pay off
reviews.comments: Purchased 3 of these. If you want a vibrant look within an hr the product will start to crease and look bad. If you want to avoid the creaseing you have to use a small amount making it so subtle and barely obvious. Would not purchase again.

reviews.headline: Color beautiful but not the smoothest
reviews.comments: The color of this product is beautiful. Makes my eyes pop. I chose the green it doesn't glide. It seems to glump I did buy the white crayon stick as well.    the white crayon stick glides much better. Maybe it's the different colors that affects the crayon.

reviews.headline: I would not buy this for myself again
reviews.comments: I like the thickness of the crayon, but I would like a smoother application and one that stays one longer without smudging.

reviews.headline: Great Eye Pencil
reviews.comments:
Great jumbo eye pencil. I like to use this pencil to highlight my eyes. The NYX brand is the only one I use for
this purpose. Love it!

reviews.headline: My new favorite eye pencils
reviews.comments:
I discovered these NYX jumbo eye pencils at Ulta in pink and green and I love how they look on my eyes. The colors aren't too bright and they stay on my eyes all days. I recently bought another eye pencil in purple. 
I'm very pleased with NYX jumbo eye pencils and all NYX products.

reviews.headline: Beautiful White Cream Shadow!
reviews.comments: I've used this for nearly a year and I love it! I use it to highlight my brow bone, inner corner, waterline, and to highlight the tip and bridge of my nose. I haven't had a good white cream shadow that was able to blend nicely and have the pigmentation that I want until I got this! The con is the longevity of it. I'd put it on and three hours+ it'll be half the pigmentation that it once was. But either way, it's great as a base, highlight, and good highlighter!

faceoff_positive.comments:
I only intended to buy essentials when i stepped into Ulta that day like some face wash and some of nyxs brow products - but they were out of what i was looking for. i have a weakness for red shadows and came across they're 'rust' pencil and fell for the color the moment i swatched it on my hand!  
An impulse buy that i definitely don't regret. Would buy again! Tried it out at home with some red pigment in the center and it's just what I've always been looking for.
faceoff_positive.headline: beautiful color!

faceoff_negative.comments:
I bought two colors, the coveted Milk to use as a base and Black Bean because its black. Black Bean was not bad but its just your average black that you can find in any brand. It wears away easily and its not a deep rich black, it smudges and runs. For sure not a HG product. 

Milk is good to use as a base, which is sadly the only thing its good for. It makes ANY color more true to pan when applied first. I find that if I use it in my waterline it smudges/runs/fades as well as when I use it for regular eyeliner. It can be difficult to apply evenly (when used as a base) and can get blotchy fast, if to much is put on. Blending it out can be a bit of a pain too, even when used with a regular primer underneath. Its not a HG base either. I think its hyped up for nothing.
faceoff_negative.headline: Milk & Black Bean
